# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Microsoft Graph (required only for /messagecenter and /servicehealth pages)
#
# Option 1 — Managed identity (recommended when hosting on Azure; no secret):
#   Assign a system- or user-assigned managed identity to the Azure host, grant
#   it the ServiceMessage.Read.All + ServiceHealth.Read.All Graph application
#   permissions, then set:
#     USE_MANAGED_IDENTITY=true
#   For a USER-assigned identity, also set its client id:
#     AZURE_CLIENT_ID=<managed-identity-client-id>
#   (On App Service / Container Apps the platform sets IDENTITY_ENDPOINT and
#   IDENTITY_HEADER automatically; on a VM the IMDS endpoint is used.)
#
# Option 2 — App registration client secret (works locally too). Easiest setup:
#   run scripts/create-entra-app.ps1 — it creates the Entra app registration,
#   adds the permissions, grants admin consent, creates a client secret, and
#   fills in the three values below. Manual setup: README.md → Setup → step 2.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# USE_MANAGED_IDENTITY=true
# AZURE_CLIENT_ID=your-user-assigned-mi-client-id
M365_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-here
M365_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret-here
M365_TENANT_ID=your-tenant-id-here

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI summarization (optional — enables the "✨ AI Insights" panel + per-item
# Summarize button on every feed page). The server auto-detects which provider
# to use based on which variables are set. Priority: Azure OpenAI → OpenAI →
# GitHub Models. Pick ONE block and leave the others blank/commented.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Option A: Azure OpenAI (recommended for Microsoft customers) ──
# AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.openai.azure.com
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your-azure-openai-key
# AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT=gpt-4o-mini
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION=2024-10-21

# ── Option B: OpenAI ──
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com

# ── Option C: GitHub Models (free tier — great for trying it out) ──
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_...
# GITHUB_MODEL=openai/gpt-4o-mini

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Server / security options (all optional)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Bind host + port. Defaults to loopback (127.0.0.1). Binding to a non-loopback
# host requires ALLOW_REMOTE_BIND=true and should only ever sit behind an
# authenticated reverse proxy on a trusted network.
# HOST=127.0.0.1
# PORT=3000
# ALLOW_REMOTE_BIND=false

# When set, the /api/empty-products admin endpoint requires this bearer token
# for BOTH read (GET) and clear (DELETE). Compared in constant time.
# ADMIN_TOKEN=change-me-to-a-long-random-string

# Set to true ONLY when running behind a trusted reverse proxy so the rate
# limiter reads the client IP from the first X-Forwarded-For entry. Leave unset
# otherwise — clients can spoof this header.
# TRUST_PROXY=false

# Comma-separated exact origins allowed for CORS (no wildcards). Unset = same-origin only.
# CORS_ORIGINS=https://portal.example.com
